<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413158>
    dc:description "FIGURES 2–7. (2) Gall asexual generation Disholcaspis edura; (3) Gall asexual generation D. spissa; 4–7 asexual generation D. quercusglobulus (4) dorsal mesosoma; (5) propodeum; (6) lateral metasoma; (7) ventral hypopygial spine." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4413158/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413160>
    dc:description "FIGURES 8–10. (8) Ventral hypopygial spine, Disholcaspis corallina; (9) ventral hypopygial spine, D. chrysolepidis; (10) Quercus sp. leaf petioles curling around a Disholcaspis sexual generation gall with one leaf removed so that you can see the gall." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4413160/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413176>
    dc:description "FIGURES 42–47. Asexual female Disholcaspis erugomamma n. sp., (42) lateral mesosoma; (43) posterior mesosoma; (44) wing; (45) lateral metasoma; (46) ventral hypopygial spine; (47) galls." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4413176/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413178>
    dc:description "FIGURES 48–53. Disholcaspis. (48) sexual female lateral habitus, D. quercusvirens, image from George Melika; (49) male lateral habitus, D. quercusvirens, image from George Melika; (50) male anterior head, D. prehensa, (51) sexual female lateral" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4413178/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

